--> <br>
<br>
If its a single mob fight, such as most epics steps, there is abosultely no reason not to use defensive, assuming you can keep agro with it up. Not using defensive on Sev, because your clerics should get used to a non-defensive tank, for when you do NToV in 12 months is just stupid imo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrexorgrimblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grexor Grimblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/24/02 12:46:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1417.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.prexus.com/harmonyofsouls/pics/hos_icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When to go Defensive</span><hr size=1> Interesting points made by Furor.. I guess I find the idea of not using a skill that makes a fight easier just to pump my ego a little hard to grasp.  Kind of like saying, yeah I could keep agro a lot better with a SoD but they are for @#%$ warriors, until you can kill Tormax with a Yak (old school) your just lazy.<br>
